# ============================================================================
# Stripe Configuration (ST01-Stripe-Account-Setup.md)
# ============================================================================
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Create a Stripe account at https://stripe.com
# 2. Navigate to Developers > API keys in your Stripe Dashboard
# 3. Ensure "Test mode" toggle is ON (orange indicator)
# 4. Copy your test API keys below
#
# SECURITY NOTES:
# - NEVER commit actual API keys to version control
# - Secret keys (sk_*) should ONLY be used server-side
# - Publishable keys (pk_*) are safe for client-side use
# - Rotate keys if they are ever exposed

# Stripe Publishable Key (Client-side - safe to expose)
# Used for creating Checkout Sessions and client-side Stripe.js
# Format: pk_test_... (test) or pk_live_... (production)
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY="pk_test_your_publishable_key_here"

# Stripe Secret Key (Server-side ONLY - NEVER expose to client)
# Used for API operations: products, prices, checkout sessions, subscriptions
# Format: sk_test_... (test) or sk_live_... (production)
# ⚠️ CRITICAL: This key grants full access to your Stripe account
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY="sk_test_your_secret_key_here"

# Stripe Webhook Secret (Server-side ONLY)
# Used to verify webhook event signatures for security
# Get from: Stripe Dashboard > Developers > Webhooks > Select endpoint > Signing secret
# Format: whsec_...
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET="whsec_your_webhook_secret_here"

# Stripe Checkout Redirect URLs
# Where users are redirected after checkout completion or cancellation
# Update these for your production domain
STRIPE_SUCCESS_URL="http://localhost:5173/account?success=true"
STRIPE_CANCEL_URL="http://localhost:5173/pricing?canceled=true"

# ============================================================================
# Stripe Product Price IDs (ST06-Configure-Stripe-Products.md)
# ============================================================================
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Go to Stripe Dashboard > Products
# 2. Create "Pro Plan" product with monthly ($29) and annual ($290) prices
# 3. Create "Enterprise Plan" product with monthly ($99) and annual ($990) prices
# 4. Copy the price IDs (format: price_xxx) for each price
# 5. Paste them below
#
# NOTE: Use test mode price IDs for development, live price IDs for production

# Pro Plan Price IDs
# Monthly: $29.00 USD with 14-day trial
STRIPE_PRICE_PRO_MONTHLY="price_your_pro_monthly_id"
# Annual: $290.00 USD with 14-day trial (2 months free)
STRIPE_PRICE_PRO_ANNUAL="price_your_pro_annual_id"

# Enterprise Plan Price IDs
# Monthly: $99.00 USD with 14-day trial
STRIPE_PRICE_ENTERPRISE_MONTHLY="price_your_enterprise_monthly_id"
# Annual: $990.00 USD with 14-day trial (2 months free)
STRIPE_PRICE_ENTERPRISE_ANNUAL="price_your_enterprise_annual_id"

# ============================================================================
